Algo 1.4.1: Sorting Linear Array using Bubble Sorting (For Ascending Order)

Bubble_sort(Array[], int N):

	START
Step 01: Reading input
	Read Array[]
Step 02: Performing Bubble Sort Procedure
	Repeat FOR I := 1 TO N-1 BY 1 DO:
		[a. Comparing each element, decrementing total elements each time by 1]
		Repeat FOR J := 1 TO N-I-1 BY 1 DO:
			[b. Comparing if greater, than swap]
			IF A[J] > A[J+1] THEN:
				SET TEMP := A[J]
				SET A[J] := A[J+1]
				SET A[J+1] := TEMP
			END IF
		END DO
	END DO
	EXIT
